  "body": "After running the fuzzer for some time, my system hit out-of-disk errors. \r\nIt had filled the disk with `/tmp/erigon-memdb-<numbers>/`, where each folder contains one `mdbx.dat` at `24KiB`, and an `mdbx.lck` at `1MiB`. It seems that each invocation of `evm` creates one \r\n\r\nExample to create one:\r\n```\r\n/home/martin/workspace/erigon-evm --json --noreturndata --nomemory statetest /tmp/00048943-mixed-1.json\r\n```\r\nI retried with `60024361821f6bcc6b8e724aed1b07531c447fce`, same issue. \r\n\r\n",
